			<ns0:name>jamesfen...@gmail.com</ns0:name><ns0:uri>/u/105008541472586726939/</ns0:uri></ns0:author><ns0:content type="html">For file IO write API, asynchronous API only seems fine(not too bad).
But for file IO read API, for applications other than handling text, it would be very painful to write all the logic to accumulate whole structure data via reading. And the performance will suck too.
So, I suggest at least add synchronous file IO read API support to nacl.
